Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.50,0:00:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I'm sure many of us here have
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,found ourselves in this
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.09,0:00:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.22,0:00:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in the bathtub, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.00,0:00:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with an amazing idea for
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.40,0:00:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.07,0:00:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps a little bit less
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.15,0:00:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,relaxing, you get a text message
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.36,0:00:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,from someone very important in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.68,0:00:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,your organization asking you to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.26,0:00:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with amazing ideas for a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.35,0:00:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,new app.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.81,0:00:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like we are going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.10,0:00:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at Timers today.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.09,0:00:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So in those situations, you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.68,0:00:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,might tell yourself, "I don't
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.13,0:00:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,have time."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.01,0:00:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You might want to dive into X
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.30,0:00:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,code, start typing out some
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.79,0:00:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Swift, but the problem with that
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.58,0:00:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is that once you get committed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.76,0:00:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to code, you're really deep into
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.58,0:00:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how your app is going to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.81,0:00:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't get much leeway to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.33,0:00:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,explore all the alternatives
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.86,0:00:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that you could.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.29,0:01:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you might want to dive into
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.38,0:01:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Sketch, and draw some really
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.93,0:01:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,detailed visuals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.56,0:01:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But again, the problem with that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.36,0:01:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is that visuals are not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.61,0:01:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.50,0:01:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We're building apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.65,0:01:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to try it as if it were
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.62,0:01:12.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a real app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.95,0:01:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So let me show you something I
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.78,0:01:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,may build after getting my CEO
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.90,0:01:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for a Timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.85,0:01:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a very basic concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.78,0:01:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I tap to add five seconds to the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.37,0:01:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.88,0:01:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make it 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.63,0:01:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I press Start, and it starts
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.55,0:01:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,counting down to zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.29,0:01:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing fancy here, just an idea
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.23,0:01:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I had about how the Timer app
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.72,0:01:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,might look.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.35,0:01:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as you might have guessed,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.46,0:01:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,from the title of this talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.50,0:01:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,this is not a real app.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.29,0:01:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a prototype, and it only
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.74,0:01:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,took me 60 seconds to build.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.67,0:01:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That is less time than it took
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.42,0:01:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,you to brush your teeth this
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.40,0:01:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,morning...hopefully [laughter].
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.56,0:01:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So why do we build prototypes?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.87,0:01:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We build prototypes to test
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.66,0:01:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.40,0:01:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Some things that seem really
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.69,0:01:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,great might turn out to be not
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.45,0:01:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so great once you try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.82,0:02:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And some things that don't
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.80,0:02:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,appear very good at first might
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.12,0:02:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,actually have some very valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.49,0:02:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,insights to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.13,0:02:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This is about saving time and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,money by making sure that when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.93,0:02:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you commit to building something
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,by writing code, designing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.83,0:02:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,assets, you're building the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.31,0:02:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.66,0:02:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We also make prototypes to get
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.83,0:02:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,new ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.69,0:02:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The act of making prototypes and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.86,0:02:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,showing them to people will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.51,0:02:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,bring new insights that will
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.67,0:02:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,help make your product even
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.65,0:02:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,better.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.16,0:02:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Designers love diagrams, so here
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.17,0:02:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is a diagram of what the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.06,0:02:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,prototyping process might look
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.19,0:02:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,like.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.15,0:02:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We make prototypes, we show them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.36,0:02:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to people, and we learn from the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.15,0:02:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.72,0:02:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do this over and over and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.46,0:02:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,over again, until we know we're
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.88,0:02:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,really making the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.19,0:02:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's start by making a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.56,0:02:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.40,0:02:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can make prototypes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone. It is about using
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.53,0:02:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,tools that you already use every
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.09,0:02:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.81,0:02:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a developer, you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.73,0:02:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,might use X code in Swift, or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.02,0:02:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.61,0:02:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a designer, you might
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.98,0:02:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,use Sketch or Illustrator.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.36,0:03:01.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if you don't code or
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,design, you can build
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.09,0:03:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,prototypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.45,0:03:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can use keynotes, or your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.22,0:03:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,favorite text processor.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about subverting your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.76,0:03:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.27,0:03:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Use tools that you use already
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.14,0:03:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,every day, and push them in new
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.76,0:03:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.50,0:03:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If it can display images, and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.96,0:03:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,respond to user interaction, you
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.48,0:03:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,can probably build prototypes
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.96,0:03:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.80,0:03:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So let me show you how I built
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.88,0:03:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the prototype we just saw
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.70,0:03:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,earlier, just using Keynotes, in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.66,0:03:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,under 60 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.07,0:03:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the video you're about to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.21,0:03:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,see is a little fast, because I
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.50,0:03:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,like to use Keynote a lot for
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.47,0:03:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of stuff, but let me
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.90,0:03:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,get you through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.50,0:03:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So I start by making my document
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the size of an iPhone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.55,0:03:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to draw the clock
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.78,0:03:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,face for my timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.14,0:03:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll notice I'm not using
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.85,0:03:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,really fancy design assets, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.71,0:03:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,just using basic Keynote shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.76,0:03:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do the same thing for the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.58,0:03:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,button, the Start button.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.19,0:03:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, just using a basic
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.38,0:03:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Keynote shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's make it green.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.93,0:03:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's make it say Start.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:03:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm adding the hand for my
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.05,0:03:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.77,0:03:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The trick I'm going to use is in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.53,0:03:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Keynote, when you rotate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.36,0:03:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,objects, they rotate around
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.58,0:04:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,their center.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.20,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So here, you see I am
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,copy/pasting the hand, moving it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.98,0:04:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to the lower part, and making it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.31,0:04:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I can group them and I can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,rotate it and it will look just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.86,0:04:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,like a hand on the timer would.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.63,0:04:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So we make it rotate to the 5
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.43,0:04:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,second mark for the first tap,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.25,0:04:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,no easing to make it look just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.56,0:04:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,like a real clock, and we add
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.20,0:04:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,another animation for the 10
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.53,0:04:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,second mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.77,0:04:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, the last animation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.29,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the hand of the timer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,rotating all the way back to the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.05,0:04:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,0 second mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.79,0:04:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And as this animation starts, we
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.40,0:04:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,make the Start button disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.50,0:04:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like that, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.46,0:04:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,prototype that we can load on an
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.19,0:04:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,iPhone, and have it look just
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.88,0:04:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,like a real app.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.52,0:04:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.47,0:04:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So now that we've made a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.21,0:04:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,prototype, we show it to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.39,0:04:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,As we show it to people, we ask
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.72,0:04:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,ourselves, how can we make it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.46,0:04:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,better?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.99,0:04:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I have some theories about what
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.67,0:04:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,will work and what won't, and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.48,0:04:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,look for evidence that supports
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.91,0:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or contradicts those theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.55,0:05:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't argue, defend, or dismiss
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.24,0:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,the feedback you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.73,0:05:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also very important to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.95,0:05:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,show your prototypes in context,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,on the device they're meant for,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.48,0:05:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in a somewhat realistic
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.39,0:05:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.74,0:05:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't test things in a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.74,0:05:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.91,0:05:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, here I ask my
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.56,0:05:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,co-worker to test the pH of a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit of water, using the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.59,0:05:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.00,0:05:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So we add the pH reagent, press
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.81,0:05:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the Start button, and start
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.12,0:05:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,shaking the test tube for 10
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.12,0:05:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.46,0:05:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So in this case, it seems to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.72,0:05:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,work pretty well, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.97,0:05:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, it is not a very
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.06,0:05:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,complicated use case.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe it would be nice to have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.47,0:05:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Timer flash, or play a sound
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.72,0:05:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end, but it seems to work
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.29,0:05:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.16,0:05:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, my friend David used to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.39,0:05:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,really good at solving the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.31,0:05:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Rubik's Cube in high school, so
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.85,0:05:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked him to see if he could
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.87,0:05:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,still solve a Rubik's Cube in
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.88,0:05:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,under 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.22,0:05:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.37,0:05:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like he's still got it,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.48,0:05:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,with time to spare, too
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.85,0:05:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[applause].
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.15,0:05:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as David was using this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.56,0:05:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,there are a number of things
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.46,0:05:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that he was telling me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He found that the Start button
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.73,0:06:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,was a little small, and hard to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.25,0:06:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,tap.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.35,0:06:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He also thought it would be nice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.73,0:06:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,if there was a countdown when
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you press Start, so he could
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.19,0:06:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,really position himself on the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.25,0:06:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Rubik's Cube, and he really
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.39,0:06:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to see the actual precise
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.93,0:06:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,time, so he could tell if he
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.17,0:06:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,beat his record or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that this opens up a lot
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.18,0:06:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,of interesting design questions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.73,0:06:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,around what we're building, and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what it should be like.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.92,0:06:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we've shown our prototypes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.13,0:06:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we take a moment to step back
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and learn from the feedback that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.33,0:06:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we have gathered.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What is working?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What is not working?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.48,0:06:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we refine what we have?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.52,0:06:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Or do we try something else
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.97,0:06:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,altogether?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.06,0:06:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps do some brainstorming to
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,come up with the next steps?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.55,0:06:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, here are some of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.27,0:06:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the questions that we got as we
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.11,0:06:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,showed our prototype.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we display the time left on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the timer, or the time elapsed?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.90,0:06:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you pause or stop the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.83,0:06:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,timer?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.29,0:06:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we show the time in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.34,0:06:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,digital form or analog form, or
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.39,0:06:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe both?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.23,0:07:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And are we building a generic
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,timer, or one for a very
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.84,0:07:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,specific purpose, like solving
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.62,0:07:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Rubik's Cubes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And many, many other questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.38,0:07:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the goal isn't to answer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.03,0:07:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all of those questions, but
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.27,0:07:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,rather to know what you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.77,0:07:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,know, so you can then
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.95,0:07:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,strategically choose what to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.46,0:07:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,pursue next.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.34,0:07:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is how I might improve this
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.33,0:07:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,prototype after showing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.95,0:07:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, David told me that the Start
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.93,0:07:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,button was small, and the Clock
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was hard to see, so I agree with
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.68,0:07:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.88,0:07:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to make it a nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.80,0:07:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,bold red, and let's make the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.80,0:07:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,hand white, just so that it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,really stands out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.26,0:07:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Start button is too small, so
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.48,0:07:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,let's do away with it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.17,0:07:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,altogether, and maybe we make
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.99,0:07:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire lower portion of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.04,0:07:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,this, creating a tap region.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.50,0:07:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's make it say Start in
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.80,0:07:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,nice, bold letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.66,0:07:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Same color as the clock to keep
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it consistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.31,0:07:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to add a finish
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.23,0:07:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,screen for my timer, so we know
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.01,0:07:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the timer is done counting down.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.75,0:07:53.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So I just add a new slide that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.14,0:07:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we navigate to automatically and
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.89,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have it say Timer Done.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.97,0:07:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like that, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.05,0:07:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,new iteration of our prototype,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.57,0:08:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can build on, and show
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.09,0:08:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.06,0:08:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Making things fast lets you
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.11,0:08:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,quickly explore a very wide
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.96,0:08:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,range of ideas and directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.08,0:08:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some more prototypes
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that I built in Keynote around
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.72,0:08:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the concept of the Timer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.32,0:08:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, some of them, as you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.04,0:08:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are aesthetic explorations
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.63,0:08:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,around what a Timer might look
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,like, or how you might interact
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,with it, while others are more
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.76,0:08:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,specific use cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.22,0:08:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Timers for developing film or
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.26,0:08:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,cooking a steak.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That is also where having a very
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.68,0:08:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,diverse team helps your process
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.40,0:08:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.83,0:08:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It will let you stumble upon
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.84,0:08:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,things you never would have on
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.99,0:08:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, my co-worker made
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.68,0:08:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,this Timer to help their child
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.09,0:08:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,brush their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.62,0:08:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we make quick interactive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.13,0:08:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,prototypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.89,0:08:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We show them to people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.06,0:08:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And we learn from the feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.87,0:08:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we do this over, and over,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.10,0:08:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and over again, until we know
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.80,0:08:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we're doing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.94,0:09:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you start by making one
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.39,0:09:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, you'll be inspired to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.35,0:09:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,make a few others.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.14,0:09:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of these things will work
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.90,0:09:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,really well, and the ideas will
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.72,0:09:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,make it mostly unchanged
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.12,0:09:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout your prototyping
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.97,0:09:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,process, and on to your final
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.30,0:09:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,product.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.55,0:09:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Most things will have some
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.63,0:09:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,aspects that work, and others
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that don't work as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.08,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be able to take those
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and modify them and recombine
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.87,0:09:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,them in new prototypes that you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.41,0:09:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,can show and explore.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.12,0:09:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, a few things won't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.09,0:09:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,work at all, and it is great
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.42,0:09:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,when that happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.40,0:09:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You've just learned something
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,very valuable about your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.24,0:09:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.39,0:09:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,spending designing time or
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.37,0:09:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,programming time building things
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.76,0:09:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that would not have worked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.55,0:09:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal is to take ideas from
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.23,0:09:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,your head into the real world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.62,0:09:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on device, in context, in front
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.65,0:09:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,of people, as fast as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As you are leaving WWDC later
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.43,0:09:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,today, here are a few things you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.72,0:09:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.52,0:09:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't make prototypes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.63,0:10:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,already, the next time you have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.95,0:10:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,an idea for an app, or future
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.52,0:10:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,for your app, make prototypes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.44,0:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Show them to your colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.99,0:10:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you already make prototypes,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.73,0:10:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.39,0:10:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.31,0:10:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Find co-workers who don't, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.98,0:10:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,show them how you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you manage a team, make
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.81,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that you're building the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.66,0:10:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,right thing, by making time for
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,prototyping as part of your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.73,0:10:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,process and culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.12,0:10:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine how wonderful it would
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.57,0:10:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,be if the next time you get a
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.03,0:10:27.43,Default,,0,0,0,,text message like this from your
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,CEO, you can reply just 60
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,seconds later with a prototype
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.02,0:10:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
